title: How to Cancel/Disable Export Feed
problem: Dealer needs to cancel or disable their export feed to a syndicator platform.
solution: Disable the export feed through the Admin Dashboard and notify the client.
steps: Log into Admin Dashboard
Click 'Clients' in the left sidebar
Search for the dealer name in the search bar
Click on the dealer's name to open their profile
Click the 'Exports' tab at the top
Find the syndicator name (e.g., 'Syndicator_Export_1')
Click the red 'Disable' button next to the feed
Confirm the action in the popup dialog
Verify the status changed to 'Inactive'
Send confirmation email to client (remember to CC the sales rep)

title: How to Activate New Export Feed
problem: Dealer wants to start exporting their inventory to a new syndicator platform.
solution: Verify order exists, then enable the export feed and provide the Feed ID.
steps: Log into Admin Dashboard
Click 'Clients' in the left sidebar
Search for the dealer name
Click on the dealer's name to open their profile
Click the 'Exports' tab
Check if the syndicator is already listed (if yes, skip to step 10)
Verify the dealer has an active order for this export
Click 'Add New Export' button
Select the syndicator from the dropdown (e.g., 'Syndicator_Export_2')
Click 'Enable' to activate the feed
Copy the Feed ID that appears (e.g., 'FEED-12345')
Send email to client with the Feed ID
CC the sales rep on all communications

title: Troubleshooting Stale/Sold Vehicles Showing in Import
problem: Import feed is showing vehicles that were already sold or outdated inventory.
solution: Force a manual refresh of the import feed and verify data with provider.
steps: Log into Admin Dashboard
Click 'Clients' in the left sidebar
Search for the dealer name
Click the 'Imports' tab
Find the provider name (e.g., 'Provider_Import_1')
Check the 'Last Updated' timestamp (should be within 4 hours)
Click 'Force Refresh' button to trigger immediate import
Wait 2-3 minutes for refresh to complete
Check if sold vehicles are now removed
If problem persists, contact the provider to verify their data feed
Send status update to client (CC the sales rep)

title: Troubleshooting Export Feed Not Updating (including verifying FTP credentials)
problem: Export feed is not showing recent inventory changes or updates. In some cases the export process runs but the syndicator fails to ingest because of outdated or incorrect FTP credentials.
solution: Check export status and connection, verify and if necessary update the FTP credentials in Admin Dashboard -> Export, test the FTP connection, and coordinate credential changes with the syndicator.
steps: Confirm the export job status and last successful run in the Admin Dashboard (Exports section).
Force an export/refresh if available to ensure latest data is generated.
Check server/export logs for errors or successful file generation and upload timestamps.
Verify the feed files were uploaded to the syndicator destination (FTP/SFTP) â€” check file timestamps and sizes.
Test FTP/SFTP connection to the syndicator using the credentials stored in Admin Dashboard -> Export (or use an FTP client).
If the connection fails or credentials are rejected, update the FTP username/password in Admin Dashboard -> Export with the latest credentials provided by the syndicator.
After updating credentials, attempt a manual export and test the FTP upload again to confirm success.
Notify the syndicator that credentials were updated and confirm they can access and ingest the latest files.
Monitor subsequent exports and confirm with the dealer that the feed updates resumed.
If problems persist, collect logs, error messages, and timestamps and escalate to platform/network team or syndicator support as needed.

version_history.change_reason: The existing article addresses feeds not updating but lacks the specific, actionable step discovered in this ticket: verifying and updating FTP credentials in Admin Dashboard -> Export and coordinating credential updates with the syndicator. The ticket shows the export itself was functioning but outdated credentials prevented syndicator ingestion. Updating the existing KB to include explicit credential checks, testing, and outreach steps will make the article more complete and increase its effectiveness.

title: Import Feed Showing Wrong Vehicle Prices
problem: Imported vehicles are displaying incorrect pricing information.
solution: Verify price mapping settings and refresh the import feed.
steps: Log into Admin Dashboard
Click 'Clients' in the left sidebar
Search for the dealer name
Click the 'Imports' tab
Find the provider name (e.g., 'Provider_Import_1')
Click 'Settings' gear icon next to the provider
Check 'Price Field Mapping' section
Verify it's set to the correct price field (e.g., 'Internet Price')
Click 'Save Settings' if you made changes
Click 'Force Refresh' to re-import with new settings
Verify a few vehicle prices are now correct
Send confirmation to client

title: Can We Have Separate Feeds for New vs Used Inventory?
problem: A dealer wants to send separate new and used vehicle feeds to the same syndicator. Clarify whether multiple feeds or separate feed IDs per syndicator are supported and how to achieve inventory-type separation.
solution: You cannot create more than one feed ID per syndicator. Instead, inventory separation (new vs used) is handled via inventory-type controls in the admin dashboard: for each syndicator you can select which inventory types to include using checkboxes. Configure those checkboxes to include only the inventory types you want the syndicator to receive.
steps: Log in to the admin dashboard.
Navigate to Syndicators (or the appropriate syndicator configuration page).
Select the syndicator (e.g., Syndicator_Export_1) you want to configure.
Locate the inventory-type checkboxes (typically labeled New, Used, CPO, etc.).
Check only the inventory types you want this syndicator to receive. Uncheck the others.
Save your changes. The single feed ID for that syndicator will now deliver only the selected inventory types.
If you need different inventory selections for multiple endpoints, contact support to discuss alternatives (e.g., different syndicator accounts or custom routing if available).

version_history.change_reason: The existing KB article states dealers can have separate feeds for new vs used inventory. The ticket resolution clarifies that as of Nov 12, 2025, dealers cannot create more than one feed ID per syndicator; instead the admin dashboard now provides per-syndicator checkboxes to select which inventory types (new/used/cpo/etc.) are included. The existing article is therefore outdated and should be updated to reflect the current behavior and admin workflow.

title: Onboarding New Client - Complete Export Feed Setup
problem: New client needs their first export feed configured from scratch.
solution: Create client profile, verify order, enable export, and provide Feed ID.
steps: Log into Admin Dashboard
Click 'Add New Client' button (top right)
Enter dealer information (Name, Address, Contact)
Click 'Create Client Profile'
Verify the dealer has an active order for the export service
Navigate to the new client's profile
Click 'Exports' tab
Click 'Add New Export' button
Select syndicator from dropdown (e.g., 'Syndicator_Export_1')
Configure inventory filter (New/Used/Both)
Click 'Enable' to activate the feed
Copy the generated Feed ID
Send welcome email with Feed ID and setup instructions
CC the sales rep and account manager

title: Check Integration/Feed Status - Verify if Feed is Active
problem: Need to quickly verify if a dealer's feed is currently active and working.
solution: Check feed status in Admin Dashboard and review recent activity.
steps: Log into Admin Dashboard
Click 'Clients' in the left sidebar
Search for the dealer name
Click on the dealer's profile
Check both 'Imports' and 'Exports' tabs
Look for green 'Active' status badge
Check 'Last Updated' timestamp (should be recent)
Review 'Activity Log' for recent successful operations
If status shows 'Inactive' or 'Error', investigate further
Reply to requester with current status and last activity time

title: Troubleshooting When Export Feed Is Up but Syndicator Isn't Ingesting (Syndicator_Export_4)
problem: Export files are being generated and delivered (FTP credentials and connection are correct), but the syndicator (Syndicator_Export_4) hasn't updated or ingested the feed for one or more days.
solution: Verify that exports are being produced and delivered successfully. If export delivery and credentials are correct, gather logs and delivery evidence, then contact the syndicator's support with the evidence and escalate as needed. Communicate clearly with the dealer about the status and expected resolution timeline.
steps: Step 1 â€” Verify export generation: Check the export job status in Admin Dashboard -> Export and confirm the feed file(s) were generated at expected intervals.
Step 2 â€” Verify FTP delivery: Test the FTP connection and confirm the latest feed file is present on the syndicator's FTP server. Confirm file timestamp and size.
Step 3 â€” Confirm credentials and config: Re-check FTP credentials and export configuration (path, file naming, schedule). Document that credentials and config are correct.
Step 4 â€” Review logs: Collect export logs and any transfer logs (timestamps, checksums) showing successful transfer. Note any error messages if present.
Step 5 â€” Check syndicator status pages/alerts: Verify whether Syndicator_Export_4 has any known outages or incidents reported on their status page or support channel.

Step 6 â€” Contact syndicator support: Open a ticket with Syndicator_Export_4 support including: a) feed name, b) dealer ID (Dealership_1), c) timestamps of generated files, d) file names, sizes and checksums, e) evidence of successful FTP transfer, f) brief description of missing ingestion/updates and duration (e.g., 3 days). Request an ETA for resolution and ask them to confirm ingestion success once resolved.

Step 7 â€” Escalate internally if needed: If syndicator does not respond within SLA or dealer impact is high, escalate to Syndication Team lead and include collected evidence and dealer contact frequency.

Step 8 â€” Communicate with dealer: Provide the dealer with a concise status update including what you checked, that the feed delivery is verified, that the issue is with the syndicator, and the expected ETA or next update.
Step 9 â€” Confirm resolution: Once syndicator confirms the fix, verify that the syndicator has ingested the latest feed and that inventory updates are reflected. Document time-to-resolution.

Step 10 â€” Post-incident notes: Add a short postmortem note to the ticket: root cause, actions taken, contact with syndicator, and preventive recommendations (e.g., monitoring alerts or automated ingestion checks).
